Doug Gregory was awarded the Distinguished Flying Cross after surviving 70 missions over Nazi-occupied Europe . 
  He only retired from his job as a stunt pilot two years ago . 
  The 92-year-old was struck by a car outside a petrol station in Hampshire . 
  He suffered a serious head injury and was flown to hospital but died two weeks later . 
  Mr Gregory had survived 70 missions against the Luftwaffe during the Second World War . 
 